1
00:00:37,410 --> 00:00:39,490
（芝加哥）

2
00:00:41,330 --> 00:00:46,120
妈妈生病了 就这么突然发生了
Mummy got sick. It happened just like that.

3
00:00:47,170 --> 00:00:50,500
没人可以帮上忙
Nobody could stop it.

4
00:00:50,670 --> 00:00:54,460
这不公平，没有什么原因
It isn't fair. There's no reason.

5
00:00:54,630 --> 00:01:00,350
再不停问原因，只会令人发疯
And if we start asking why, we'll go crazy.

6
00:01:22,710 --> 00:01:27,620
只要放进任何一个微波炉 五分钟就可以了
Five minutes in the microwave. Any one of them.

7
00:01:29,550 --> 00:01:32,910
你知道怎样弄果汁吗？
Do you know how to make juice?

8
00:01:35,430 --> 00:01:39,420
放进微波炉五分钟
Microwave. Five minutes.

9
00:01:55,240 --> 00:01:59,730
给，这是我的心理医生 给他打个电话吧
Here. It's my shrink. Call him.

10
00:02:08,790 --> 00:02:12,960
这是丧偶互助会
Loss of Spouse Support Group.

11
00:02:13,130 --> 00:02:18,590
芝加哥癌症病人家属支援会 父母失去另一半的
Chicago Cancer Family Network. Parents without Partners.

12
00:02:18,760 --> 00:02:23,130
拥抱自己，拥抱朋友 拥抱一位心理医生
"Hug Yourself", "Hug a Friend", "Hug a Shrink"...

13
00:02:23,310 --> 00:02:29,230
努力工作，工作能拯救你 唯有工作能帮你度过这状况
Work hard, that'll save you. Only work will see you through this.

14
00:02:34,280 --> 00:02:39,490
别介意 一位刚失去妻子的男人就会这样
Don't mind him, he's just a guy who's lost his wife.

15
00:02:43,580 --> 00:02:47,820
我想我真正需要的是改变
What I think we really need is... change.

16
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:53,420
好主意，放几周假，跟乔纳去钓个鱼
Good idea. Take a few weeks off, take Jonah fishing.

17
00:02:55,220 --> 00:02:59,630
不，是真的改变，新城市
No, real change. A new city.

18
00:03:00,680 --> 00:03:05,720
一个新地方 让我不再想起玛吉的地方
Some place where I don't think of Maggie at every corner.

19
00:03:06,690 --> 00:03:08,770
（瑞格里球场 芝加哥《小熊队》球场）

20
00:03:13,360 --> 00:03:14,480
你要去哪？
Where are you gonna go?

21
00:03:19,740 --> 00:03:22,080
我在考虑去西雅图
I was thinking about Seattle.

22
00:03:22,910 --> 00:03:27,910
过几个月，你会再和女人约会 你会遇到心仪的对象的
In a few months, you'll be seeing women. You'll meet someone.

23
00:03:28,090 --> 00:03:34,880
对，向前看，这正是我想做的 几个月后，我会复原，重新长个心
Move on, fine, that's what I'll do. I'll just grow a new heart.

24
00:03:35,380 --> 00:03:41,300
-山姆，对不起，我不是这意思 -我知道，只是有些事情一生一次足矣
- Sam, I'm sorry, I didn't mean... - I know. But it can't happen twice.

25
00:03:41,920 --> 00:03:43,170
?Jimmy Dante: "As Time Goes By"?

26
00:03:43,340 --> 00:03:47,140
?You must remember this, ?
?A kiss is still a kiss ?

27
00:03:47,850 --> 00:03:50,260
?A sigh is just a sigh ?

28
00:03:53,890 --> 00:03:58,020
?The fundamental things apply ?

29
00:03:58,940 --> 00:04:00,940
?As time goes by ?

30
00:04:05,530 --> 00:04:08,030
?And when two lovers woo ?

31
00:04:08,780 --> 00:04:10,950
?They still say "I love you" ?

32
00:04:11,580 --> 00:04:14,080
?On that you can rely ?

33
00:04:17,710 --> 00:04:21,630
?No matter what the future brings ?

34
00:04:22,840 --> 00:04:24,920
?As time goes by ?

35
00:04:29,640 --> 00:04:32,220
?Moonlight and love songs ?

36
00:04:32,770 --> 00:04:34,640
?Never out of date ?

37
00:04:35,690 --> 00:04:37,730
?Hearts full of passion ?

38
00:04:38,310 --> 00:04:40,440
?Jealousy and hate ?

39
00:04:41,400 --> 00:04:46,110
?Woman needs man ?
?And man must have his mate ?

40
00:04:46,740 --> 00:04:50,780
?That no one can deny ?

41
00:04:52,700 --> 00:04:55,080
?It's still the same old story ?

42
00:04:55,370 --> 00:04:58,040
?A fight for love and glory ?

43
00:04:58,580 --> 00:05:01,040
?A case of do or die ?

44
00:05:04,590 --> 00:05:09,180
?The world ?
?Will always welcome lovers ?

45
00:05:10,680 --> 00:05:16,600
?As time goes by ?

46
00:05:21,040 --> 00:05:22,370
（巴尔的摩 18个月后）

47
00:05:30,920 --> 00:05:36,040
-红发的高女人是你的表姐艾琳 -一脸失望那个就是她
- The tall redhead is cousin Irene.  - You'll see her disappointed look.

48
00:05:36,220 --> 00:05:43,010
-哈洛则是跟女秘书有染 -直到艾琳的狗病死
- Harold ran off with the secretary. - Until Irene had the dog put down.

49
00:05:43,180 --> 00:05:48,020
你的哥哥丹尼斯是教授 在约翰斯·霍普金斯
Your brother Dennis is professor at Johns Hopkins.

50
00:05:48,190 --> 00:05:53,810
-她老婆是…贝琪 -世上最难缠的人
- He's married to... Betsy. - The most competitive woman ever.

51
00:05:53,990 --> 00:05:58,480
-我怎能记住那么多事情呢？ -华特，你可以的
- How will I remember all this? - Walter, you will!

52
00:06:10,590 --> 00:06:15,080
-你的米顿叔叔赔掉所有钱 -还有其他人的钱
- Uncle Milton lost all his money... - And some other people's.

53
00:06:15,260 --> 00:06:19,840
因为骗局，更别提国税局或监狱
...in a pyramid scheme. Don't mention the IRS or the prisons.

54
00:06:20,010 --> 00:06:23,380
你妈叫芭芭拉 你爸是克里夫
Your mother's Barbara, your father's Cliff...

55
00:06:23,560 --> 00:06:27,430
-我爸收集电动火车 -真的？
- He has electric trains. - Really?

56
00:06:27,610 --> 00:06:30,520
我算乘龙快婿吗？
Am I what they had in mind?

57
00:06:30,690 --> 00:06:34,940
华特，他们会喜欢你的
Walter, they're gonna love you!

58
00:06:37,450 --> 00:06:42,530
大家注意！ 安妮有事要宣布
Everybody, Annie has an announcement.

59
00:06:42,710 --> 00:06:46,450
华特和我订婚了
Walter and I are engaged.

60
00:06:51,090 --> 00:06:54,670
谢谢，谢谢
Thank you. Thank you.

61
00:07:00,060 --> 00:07:02,590
恭喜了，华特
Congratulations, Walter.

62
00:07:04,350 --> 00:07:06,470
上帝保佑你
Bless you!

63
00:07:08,110 --> 00:07:13,150
-你还好吧？ -大概是花
- Are you all right? - Maybe it's the flowers.

64
00:07:13,320 --> 00:07:17,650
-那把花移开 -不，我要打喷嚏了
- We'll move them. - No! I feel terrible, sneezing now.

65
00:07:17,830 --> 00:07:22,910
-偏偏这时候打喷嚏 -他对什么都过敏
- This is a very important moment. - He's allergic to everything.

66
00:07:23,080 --> 00:07:26,570
我对蜜蜂过敏
Bees. I'm allergic to bees.

67
00:07:26,750 --> 00:07:32,500
不管哪种蜜蜂 我们随身携带肾上腺素
He's allergic to all bees. We have to take adrenalin with us.

68
00:07:32,670 --> 00:07:39,140
-吃一颗小果仁 -我的脑袋就会肿胀，然后会昏过去
- If he eats just a bit of a nut... - My head swells, and I drop dead.

69
00:07:39,310 --> 00:07:43,510
-哈洛碰到蜜蜂也一样 -我和你妈结婚时吃鲑鱼
- It's the same with him and bees. - We had salmon at our wedding.

70
00:07:43,690 --> 00:07:49,480
-那可是婚礼的必备佳肴 -我对鲑鱼不会过敏
- A wedding without salmon is... - I'm not allergic to salmon.

71
00:07:49,650 --> 00:07:52,140
但是也难讲
But you never know.

72
00:07:52,320 --> 00:07:56,440
-没错 -哈洛不是每次都对蜜蜂过敏
- You never know. - He wasn't always allergic to bees.

73
00:07:56,620 --> 00:08:03,910
-我们开香槟是为了庆祝什么？ -庆祝米顿叔叔假释
- What did we do with our champagne? - Uncle Milton's parole.

74
00:08:04,080 --> 00:08:09,330
-安妮，你什么时候结婚？ -六月初，在花园举行
- When are you getting married? - Early June, in the garden.

75
00:08:09,500 --> 00:08:16,500
-哈洛和蜜蜂怎么办？ -我对蜜蜂过敏
- What about Harold and bees? - I'm allergic to bees.

76
00:08:16,680 --> 00:08:20,390
冷鲜鱼、黄瓜沙拉、草莓
Cold salmon, cucumber salad, strawberries.

77
00:08:20,560 --> 00:08:25,720
我对草莓过敏
I'm afraid I am allergic to strawberries.

78
00:08:26,900 --> 00:08:30,010
你没关系吗？
Is this all right with you?

79
00:08:30,190 --> 00:08:36,030
今天我是全世界 最幸运的人
I'm the luckiest man-man-man on the face of the earth-earth-earth.

80
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:42,240
-陆·葛瑞的台词是… -《Pride of the Yankees》…
- That's Lou Gehrig's line from... - Pride of the Yankees.

81
00:08:42,410 --> 00:08:47,160
-《Pride of the Yankees》里头的 -棒球电影，这句话很经典
- Pride of the Yankees! - Baseball. An historical reference.

82
00:08:47,330 --> 00:08:52,080
我提议举杯贺喜 敬我妹妹
I would like to propose a toast. To my kid sister!

83
00:08:52,260 --> 00:08:56,220
敬华特和我的宝贝
To Walter and my baby.

84
00:08:59,600 --> 00:09:03,430
大家快吃，菜都凉了
Please eat, before it gets cold.

85
00:09:06,020 --> 00:09:11,980
找到了，历史学会想要 我都不肯给
Here it is. I wouldn't give it to the Historical Society.

86
00:09:12,150 --> 00:09:16,900
-哦，妈！ -我知道这款式又在流行了
- Oh, Mum... - These things are back in fashion.

87
00:09:17,070 --> 00:09:20,240
外婆的结婚礼服
Grandmother's dress.

88
00:09:21,410 --> 00:09:27,370
-他人不错 -我知道，他很棒吧？
- He's a lovely man, Annie. - He is, isn't he?

89
00:09:27,630 --> 00:09:34,210
而且是优秀运动员 我们要去华盛顿特区见他的父母
And he's a wonderful athlete. We're going to DC to see his parents.

90
00:09:34,380 --> 00:09:38,500
-你们怎么认识的？ -说来可笑
- How did it happen? - It's silly, really.

91
00:09:38,680 --> 00:09:43,850
我们在公司见过 他是出版商代表
I'd seen him at the office. He's the associate publisher.

92
00:09:44,020 --> 00:09:47,680
有一天我们刚巧 向同一家店订三明治
We had both ordered sandwiches...

93
00:09:47,860 --> 00:09:52,020
他拿到我那会令他过敏的 生菜番茄全麦包
...and he got my tomato on wheat, which he's allergic to.

94
00:09:52,190 --> 00:09:56,650
我拿到他的生菜番茄白面包 太神奇了，对吗？
And I got his tomato on white. Amazing, isn't it?

95
00:09:56,820 --> 00:10:01,820
每天做多少决定 随便一个便能改变你的一生
You make a million decisions, and a sandwich changes your life.

96
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:04,740
命中注定
Destiny takes a hand.

97
00:10:04,920 --> 00:10:10,630
我们不能接受不如意的事情发生 所以才发明命运
We invented destiny, because we don't want things to be accidental.

98
00:10:10,800 --> 00:10:15,920
但你怎解释你们叫了 几乎同样的东西，除了面包外？
Then why did you order the same sandwich except for the bread?

99
00:10:16,090 --> 00:10:23,060
有多少人只吃生菜番茄三明治 连点肉都不加？
How many people like tomato without something else, like tuna?

100
00:10:23,270 --> 00:10:27,140
这不是预兆，纯属巧合
It wasn't a sign. It was a coincidence.

101
00:10:27,310 --> 00:10:31,600
我和家人到大西洋城 你爸在那当侍者
I was in Atlantic City, where Cliff was a waiter.

102
00:10:31,780 --> 00:10:36,240
他当晚恰好与人调班
He wasn't supposed to work that night. What if he hadn't?

103
00:10:36,410 --> 00:10:44,250
他请我到码头来午夜漫步 我说过上千次了，不过我才不管
He asked me to take a midnight walk. I told you this a million times.

104
00:10:44,420 --> 00:10:52,630
他握着我的手 我看着，分不出谁是谁的手指
He held my hand. I looked down and couldn't tell our fingers apart.

105
00:10:52,800 --> 00:10:57,380
-我心里便明白了 -什么？
- And I knew. - What?

106
00:10:59,100 --> 00:11:04,720
-什么？ -魔力，是魔力
- What? - It was magic.

107
00:11:05,310 --> 00:11:06,640
这就是魔力
Magic.

108
00:11:06,810 --> 00:11:13,940
我知道我们将终生幸福厮守 就像你对华特一样
I knew we'd be together forever. Just like you and Walter.

109
00:11:14,110 --> 00:11:18,480
华特，挺正式的名字
Walter. It's quite a formal name.

110
00:11:19,240 --> 00:11:25,410
我还知道我和你爸…
I knew that your father and I would have a wonderful time in...

111
00:11:25,580 --> 00:11:29,080
在床上会很合的来 你们是这么叫的吧
...the sack, I believe you call it.

112
00:11:29,250 --> 00:11:35,540
是过了几年才水乳交融
It took years before it worked like clockwork. It takes time.

113
00:11:35,720 --> 00:11:40,840
-我们已经… -没关系，感觉如何？
- We already... - Fine, fine. How's it working?

114
00:11:41,020 --> 00:11:46,060
-水乳交融 -喔，亲爱的
- Like clockwork. - Oh, honey...

115
00:11:48,360 --> 00:11:53,150
-这是预兆 -你又不信
- It's a sign. - You don't believe in signs.

116
00:11:57,950 --> 00:12:02,240
他们很喜欢你，如我所料
They loved you. I told you they would.

117
00:12:02,410 --> 00:12:05,780
-我爱你 -我爱你，华特
- I love you. - I love you, Walter.

118
00:12:07,630 --> 00:12:12,870
-你有小名吗？ -没有
Did anyone ever call you anything other than Walter?

119
00:12:13,050 --> 00:12:19,420
-小时候也没有？ -没有
- Not even when you were young? - Not even when I was young.

120
00:12:19,600 --> 00:12:24,310
-确定不搭我的车回去吗？ -我周五怎么回巴尔的摩？
- Don't you want to drive with me? - Then I can't get back on Friday.

121
00:12:24,480 --> 00:12:30,390
我把送你继母的礼忘在屋里了 等我们老了
I forgot your stepmother's present. When we're old and gray...

122
00:12:30,570 --> 00:12:36,780
你得提醒我戴假牙 这样我出门就不会忘了
...you must remind me to put my teeth in, so I don't go out without them.

123
00:12:36,950 --> 00:12:39,860
-我等你 -等我，好
- I'll wait. - You'll wait? Oh, right.

124
00:12:40,040 --> 00:12:45,220
别等了，你先走吧 我就比你晚10分钟
No, go ahead. We're late anyway. I'll be ten minutes behind you.

125
00:12:45,220 --> 00:12:46,760
?"Sleigh Ride"?

126
00:12:46,930 --> 00:12:49,050
?Sleigh bells jingle-ing ?
?Ring ting tingle-ing too ?

127
00:12:49,220 --> 00:12:50,760
?Horses, horses, horses ?

128
00:12:50,930 --> 00:12:53,270
?It's lovely weather ?
?For a sleigh ride together with you ?

129
00:12:53,430 --> 00:12:54,260
?Giddy-up, giddy-up ?

130
00:12:54,260 --> 00:12:54,850
（华盛顿）

131
00:12:54,850 --> 00:12:57,940
?The snow is falling ?
?And friends are calling "Yoo Hoo" ?

132
00:12:58,100 --> 00:13:00,860
?Friends are calling "Yoo Hoo" ?
?Ding-a-ling-a-ling ?

133
00:13:01,020 --> 00:13:03,610
?Sleigh ride together with you ?
?Horse, horses, horses ?

134
00:13:03,780 --> 00:13:04,860
?Horse, horses ?

135
00:13:05,030 --> 00:13:06,490
?Rogers and Dale Evans: "Jingle Bells"

136
00:13:06,660 --> 00:13:09,450
?Jingle bells, jingle bells ?
?Jingle all the way ?

137
00:13:09,620 --> 00:13:13,410
?Oh, what fun, it is to ride ?
?In a one horse open sleigh, hey ?

138
00:13:13,580 --> 00:13:15,330
?Jingle bells ?

139
00:13:15,820 --> 00:13:18,660
欢迎收听“感情世界”
Welcome to "You and Emotions."

140
00:13:18,830 --> 00:13:24,540
我是玛莎·菲尔斯通医生 由芝加哥向全美播送
I'm Dr. Marcia Fieldstone, broadcasting live from Chicago.

141
00:13:24,710 --> 00:13:30,540
今晚我们谈愿望与梦想 你这个圣诞节有何愿望？
Tonight we'll talk about wishes. What's your wish this Christmas?

142
00:13:30,710 --> 00:13:35,420
有何愿望？ 我的愿望是转台
My wish is to change the station.

143
00:13:35,590 --> 00:13:40,840
-医生与你的主题是“你的脾脏” -下辈子吧
- And now: "You and your spleen." - Not on your life.

144
00:13:41,020 --> 00:13:45,760
接下来“圣诞铃声”倒着唱 由新泽西合唱团呈献
Coming up, "Jingle Bells" backwards, sung by...

145
00:13:45,940 --> 00:13:50,100
-西雅图，说吧 -我叫乔纳…
- Seattle, go ahead. - This is Jonah...

146
00:13:50,280 --> 00:13:54,990
不用说姓氏 你的声音很年轻，几岁了？
No last names, Jonah. How old are you?

147
00:13:55,160 --> 00:13:58,190
-八岁 -怎么这么晚还没睡？
- I'm eight. - You're up late.

148
00:13:58,370 --> 00:14:04,080
-在西雅图不晚 -对，你的圣诞愿望是什么？
- It's not so late in Seattle. - You're right. What's your wish?

149
00:14:04,250 --> 00:14:09,910
-不为我，是为我爸，他需要新妻子 -你不喜欢现在这个？
- My dad needs a new wife. - You don't like the one he has?

150
00:14:10,090 --> 00:14:14,080
-问题是他没有！ -你妈呢？
- He doesn't have one. - Where's your mum?

151
00:14:14,260 --> 00:14:19,920
-她死了 -谁会相信有这种事
- She died. - Well, who can believe this?

152
00:14:20,100 --> 00:14:25,890
-我很难过，但我爸比我还糟 -你和他谈过吗？
- I've been sad, but Dad's worse. - Have you talked to him about it?

153
00:14:26,060 --> 00:14:31,480
没有，这会让他更伤心
No, that makes him sadder.

154
00:14:31,650 --> 00:14:34,360
我了解，乔纳 你爸现在在家吗？
Jonah, is your dad home?

155
00:14:34,530 --> 00:14:39,190
-在忙吗？ -不忙，他在甲板上
- Is he busy? - No, he's out on the deck.

156
00:14:39,370 --> 00:14:42,530
我可以帮忙 但要他听电话
Can't you ask him to talk to me?

157
00:14:42,710 --> 00:14:48,580
-坏女人！挂上，乔纳，别听她的 -不行，他会杀了我
- Wretched woman! Hang up, Jonah! - No, he'd kill me.

158
00:14:48,750 --> 00:14:53,590
相信我，乔纳，他知道你关心 他就不会生气
He won't be angry when he hears how concerned you are about him.

159
00:14:53,760 --> 00:14:59,000
