01:04:12,420 --> 01:04:17,880
天气晴朗 可望准时飞抵西雅图
The weather is clear and we'll be in Seattle on schedule.

641
01:04:18,050 --> 01:04:25,930
-你讨厌飞行吗？ -对，我刚向我要嫁的人撒了大谎
- Don't you hate flying? - Yes, and I've told a terrible lie.

642
01:04:26,100 --> 01:04:29,390
你觉得这是不是 一种背叛？
Is any lie a betrayal?

643
01:04:29,570 --> 01:04:33,400
我是在说飞行
I said flying.

644
01:04:39,740 --> 01:04:44,160
-谢谢你送我来 -他喜欢飞机
- Thanks for bringing me here. - He likes the planes.

645
01:04:44,330 --> 01:04:51,120
回来送你个纪念品 雪球好吗？摇一摇雪花就飘落
Can I bring you back a souvenir? Maybe one of these snow globes?

646
01:04:51,300 --> 01:04:56,130
我很喜欢，谢谢
Sure, I'd really like that. Thank you so much.

647
01:04:57,550 --> 01:05:01,170
-他才八岁 -他很厉害
- He's eight. - He's good at it.

648
01:05:01,350 --> 01:05:06,390
报导说八岁的孩子都这样 是很正常的
I've read an article about it. Children are hideous at that age.

649
01:05:06,560 --> 01:05:13,480
等我回来后 或许我俩可以单独聚聚，如何？
Maybe when I come back, the two of us ought to spend some time alone.

650
01:05:17,990 --> 01:05:21,110
-再见，再见，乔纳 -再见
Bye. Bye, Jonah.

651
01:05:26,380 --> 01:05:28,580
乔纳
Jonah.

652
01:05:28,750 --> 01:05:32,250
听着，你不了解维多莉亚
Listen, you don't know Victoria.

653
01:05:32,420 --> 01:05:37,540
我也不了解 对我来说她是个谜
In fact she's a mystery to me too.

654
01:05:37,720 --> 01:05:41,760
她常甩头发，为什么？
She tosses her hair a lot. Why?

655
01:05:41,930 --> 01:05:46,930
抽筋还是该剪头发？ 她该用发夹夹住对吗？
Is it a twitch? Does she need a haircut or a barrette?

656
01:05:48,570 --> 01:05:55,980
我想搞清楚这些事 所以才会跟她约会
I'd like to understand these things. And that's why I'm dating her.

657
01:05:56,160 --> 01:06:01,530
约会而已 不是同居或娶她
Just dating. I'm not living with her. I'm not marrying her.

658
01:06:01,700 --> 01:06:05,240
你能了解这差别吗？
Can you appreciate the difference?

659
01:06:05,420 --> 01:06:10,040
单身贵族都这么做 先尝试彼此是否适应
That's what single people do. They see how other people fit.

660
01:06:10,210 --> 01:06:16,800
互相调整，没有人完美无缺 根本没完美这回事
Everyone's an adjustment. There's no such thing as a perfect...

661
01:06:32,150 --> 01:06:34,480
走吧
Come on.

662
01:06:36,280 --> 01:06:42,870
爸，我和杰西卡谈到未来 她说你和安妮在前世认识
Dad, Jessica says you knew Annie in another life.

663
01:06:43,040 --> 01:06:47,830
写信那个 你们上辈子没有在一起
The one who wrote us. But you never got together in that life.

664
01:06:48,000 --> 01:06:53,920
就像缺角的拼图 两人在一起才完整
Your hearts will be a complete puzzle once you're together.

665
01:06:54,090 --> 01:07:00,930
我年幼纯洁 所以我比较能接触宇宙力量
I know that because I'm young and pure, in touch with cosmic forces.

666
01:07:01,100 --> 01:07:06,640
谁告诉你这些的？ 我郑重劝你别娶杰西卡
Who told you that? I sure hope you're not marrying Jessica.

667
01:07:07,100 --> 01:07:10,520
?Harry Connick Jr.: "A Wink and a Smile"?

668
01:07:13,110 --> 01:07:17,230
?I remember the days ?
?Of just keeping time ?

669
01:07:17,650 --> 01:07:23,200
?Of hanging around ?
?In sleepy towns forever ?

670
01:07:24,330 --> 01:07:27,620
?Back roads empty for miles ?

671
01:07:30,250 --> 01:07:34,340
?Well, you can't have a dream ?
?And cut it to fit ?

672
01:07:35,000 --> 01:07:37,840
?But when I saw you, I knew ?

673
01:07:38,670 --> 01:07:44,140
?We'd go together ?
?Like a wink and a smile ?

674
01:07:48,270 --> 01:07:51,350
?Leave your old jalopy ?

675
01:07:52,150 --> 01:07:55,150
?By the railroad track ?

676
01:07:56,570 --> 01:08:00,240
?We'll get a hip double-dip tip-toppy ?

677
01:08:00,780 --> 01:08:03,860
?Two-seat Pontiac ?

678
01:08:06,280 --> 01:08:10,830
?So you can rev her up ?
?Don't go slow ?

679
01:08:11,040 --> 01:08:14,330
?It's only green lights and all rights ?

680
01:08:14,830 --> 01:08:20,670
?Let's go together ?
?With a wink and a smile ?

681
01:08:35,310 --> 01:08:38,230
?Give me a wink and a smile ?

682
01:08:50,290 --> 01:08:54,620
?We go together ?
?Like a wink and a smile ?

683
01:08:58,880 --> 01:09:01,710
?Now my heart is music ?

684
01:09:02,340 --> 01:09:05,510
?Such a simple song ?

685
01:09:06,930 --> 01:09:10,560
?Sing it again ?
?The notes never end ?

686
01:09:11,270 --> 01:09:14,270
?This is where I belong ?

687
01:09:15,100 --> 01:09:17,150
?Just the sound of your voice ?

688
01:09:17,400 --> 01:09:19,190
?The light in your eyes ?

689
01:09:19,690 --> 01:09:23,490
?We're so far away from yesterday ?

690
01:09:23,990 --> 01:09:29,910
?Together with a wink and a smile ?

691
01:09:32,750 --> 01:09:35,410
?We go together ?

692
01:09:36,500 --> 01:09:40,460
?Like a wink and a smile ?

693
01:09:50,320 --> 01:09:55,150
-我看着他陪他儿子在海边玩 -跟他讲话没有？
- I watched them play at the beach.  - Did you talk to him?

694
01:09:55,320 --> 01:09:58,910
我不敢
Couldn't do it.

695
01:09:59,080 --> 01:10:04,790
-我怎么来的？ -你撒了个谎搭上飞机
- How did I get here? - You lied and got on a plane.

696
01:10:06,040 --> 01:10:13,380
-我明天去找他谈 -好，再见
- I'm going to talk to him tomorrow. - Okay. Good. Goodbye.

697
01:10:13,550 --> 01:10:16,960
贝琪
Beck.

698
01:10:17,640 --> 01:10:23,470
-这么做是不是很疯狂？ -不，这就是奇妙之处
- Is this crazy? - No, that's the weirdest part.

699
01:10:23,640 --> 01:10:29,760
-谢谢，我爱你 -我也爱你
- Thank you. I love you. - I love you too.

700
01:11:32,170 --> 01:11:36,460
见到你真开心 葛瑞格在哪里？
It's good to see you. Where's Greg?

701
01:11:59,370 --> 01:12:01,950
你好
Hello.

702
01:12:02,160 --> 01:12:03,740
你好

703
01:12:10,130 --> 01:12:14,500
-然后呢？ -我就走了
- Then what? - I left, obviously.

704
01:12:14,680 --> 01:12:20,420
-你站在路中央？ -记得梦到自己赤裸？
- You were in the street? - It was like walking around naked.

705
01:12:20,600 --> 01:12:26,260
-我喜欢这个梦 -也比不上我的这么丢人
- I love that dream. - This was more humiliating.

706
01:12:26,440 --> 01:12:30,480
他看到你了？面对面？
But he saw you. You were face to face.

707
01:12:30,650 --> 01:12:37,490
他说“你好” 我只说得出“你好”
He said hello. And all I could say was hello.

708
01:12:38,410 --> 01:12:43,990
-我只说得出“你好” -这是个好预兆
- All I could say was hello. - It's a sign.

709
01:12:44,160 --> 01:12:49,280
表示我这部片看太多遍了
It's a sign that I've watched this movie too many times.

710
01:12:49,460 --> 01:12:56,080
我好笨！听到广播后 我就像个蠢蛋
From the minute I heard that program I've been a complete jerk.

711
01:12:56,260 --> 01:13:00,130
-你不是蠢蛋 -谢谢，白痴好了
- You're not a jerk. - Thank you. An idiot!

712
01:13:00,310 --> 01:13:06,050
-你又不知道她是谁 -我有她的照片
- You don't know who she was. - I have a picture of her.

713
01:13:06,230 --> 01:13:12,570
你看，西雅图的侦探社给我的 在这里，一模一样
The detective sent it to me. See, that's what she looks like.

714
01:13:13,450 --> 01:13:18,570
-这是张背影 -是她，而他迷恋她
- It's her back. - It's her and he's crazy about her.

715
01:13:18,740 --> 01:13:23,660
这是什么？ 西雅图寄来的
What's this? It's from Seattle.

716
01:13:30,710 --> 01:13:33,420
贝琪
Becky.

717
01:13:34,510 --> 01:13:37,970
我替你把信寄了
So I mailed your letter.

718
01:13:38,680 --> 01:13:44,720
“亲爱的安妮 谢谢你的来信，你似乎很正点”
"Dear Annie. Thanks for your letter. You sound neat.

719
01:13:48,020 --> 01:13:54,360
“我们很高兴情人节与你见面 并看看是否…”
We're excited about meeting you in New York and seeing if we are...

720
01:13:54,530 --> 01:13:57,820
“MFEO”
...M-F-E-O.

721
01:13:57,990 --> 01:14:02,200
“再见 西雅图夜未眠”
See you soon. Sleepless in Seattle."

722
01:14:02,370 --> 01:14:05,160
MFEO？
M-F-E-O?

723
01:14:08,210 --> 01:14:11,830
是彼此合适
Made for each other.

724
01:14:12,010 --> 01:14:15,170
蛮俏皮的
It's cute. Like a little clue.

725
01:14:19,760 --> 01:14:23,130
他文笔奇差，无所谓啦
So he can't write. Big deal.

726
01:14:23,310 --> 01:14:28,980
语文能力被过分重视 多要求是自寻苦恼
Verbal ability is overrated in guys. Our need for it leads to trouble.

727
01:14:29,150 --> 01:14:34,190
-我要回去找华特 -那这封信呢？
- I'm going to run back to Walter. - And the letter?

728
01:14:34,360 --> 01:14:39,150
信是之前写的 是认识那女人前写的
It was written before I went out there. Before the 'ho.

729
01:14:41,790 --> 01:14:48,780
问题是她看来不像个坏女人 倒像是个亲切的朋友
But she didn't look like a 'ho. She looked like one of our friends.

730
01:14:52,510 --> 01:14:58,300
-你在机场看到她的？ -仿佛我早就认识她，奇怪
- You saw her in the airport too? - It was like I knew her.

731
01:14:58,470 --> 01:15:03,890
-像似曾相识？ -非常法式似曾相识的情节
- Like a d茅j脿-vu? - It was very d茅j脿-vu-ish.

732
01:15:04,060 --> 01:15:09,730
-至少你开始约会了 -就这么一个
- At least you're seeing people. - Well, only one.

733
01:15:09,900 --> 01:15:14,020
-维多莉亚 -你不喜欢她？
- Victoria. - You don't like her?

734
01:15:14,200 --> 01:15:19,490
-她笑起来像土狼 -是吗？
- She laughs like a hyena. - Is this true?

735
01:15:19,660 --> 01:15:23,820
没有…有一点 说出你干的好事
Sort of. Tell them what you did.

736
01:15:24,000 --> 01:15:27,240
电台的事，说呀
Tell them about the radio show.

737
01:15:27,420 --> 01:15:31,160
平安夜那天 他打电话给电台
Christmas Eve he calls a radio show.

738
01:15:31,340 --> 01:15:38,210
-说我需要新老婆 -真的？好感人
- And tells them I need a new wife. - That's so sweet.

739
01:15:38,390 --> 01:15:42,470
现在又有一个 迷人的女人来信
Now he's obsessed with a woman who wrote me.

740
01:15:42,640 --> 01:15:45,220
她约我在帝国大厦顶楼见面
She wants to meet me on top of Empire State.

741
01:15:45,440 --> 01:15:47,850
在情人节时
On Valentines Day.

742
01:15:48,020 --> 01:15:53,640
就像那部电影《An Affair to Remember》没看过吗？
It's like that movie. An Affair to Remember.

743
01:15:53,820 --> 01:15:58,910
加里·格兰特和黛博拉·范儿 是儿还是尔？
Cary Grant and Deborah Kerr. Is that "car" or "cur"?

744
01:16:02,250 --> 01:16:07,990
他们约好在帝国大厦 顶楼见面，但她被车撞了
They were to meet at the Empire State, but she got hit by a taxi.

745
01:16:08,170 --> 01:16:13,040
他等了又等 那天下着雨
He waited and waited. And it was raining.

746
01:16:13,220 --> 01:16:19,680
结果… 她太好强，不想让他知道自己…
Then she's too proud to tell him that she's...

747
01:16:22,060 --> 01:16:27,930
跛了，他也倔强地 不肯找出她不来的原因
...crippled. And he's too proud to find out why she doesn't come.

748
01:16:28,110 --> 01:16:31,970
但他还是去找她
But he comes to see her anyway.

749
01:16:32,150 --> 01:16:36,860
他去找她时…
It's amazing when he visits her.

750
01:16:37,030 --> 01:16:41,740
没注意她未起身寒暄
He doesn't notice that she doesn't get up to say hello.

751
01:16:41,910 --> 01:16:45,150
他句句讽刺
And he's very bitter.

752
01:16:45,330 --> 01:16:50,200
当他准备走掉 不知道她为何…
You think he's going to walk out and never know why.

753
01:16:50,380 --> 01:16:58,590
一直盖着毯子蜷在沙发上
She's just lying there with a blanket over her shrivelled legs.

754
01:17:00,680 --> 01:17:03,890
-你还好吧？ -她没事
- Are you all right? - She's fine.

755
01:17:04,060 --> 01:17:10,520
他突然说…我看到画了 他走到卧房
Then he says, "I saw the painting," and goes into the bedroom.

756
01:17:10,690 --> 01:17:14,650
看一眼，出来，再看着她
And he comes out and looks at her.

757
01:17:14,820 --> 01:17:19,320
他发现了，两人相拥
And they just know and hug and it's so...

758
01:17:19,490 --> 01:17:23,110
-那是女人看的电影 -对啊
- That's a chick's movie. - I'd say so.

759
01:17:23,290 --> 01:17:29,160
-谁会听听广播就写信来？ -有好几百封呢
- Who'd write a guy from the radio? - I got hundreds of letters.

760
01:17:29,340 --> 01:17:34,050
-饥不择食 -要个好男人，怎算是饥不择食？
- Desperate women. - Is wanting a nice guy desperate?

761
01:17:34,220 --> 01:17:39,680
超过四十岁要结婚 比被恐怖份子杀死的机率还低…
It's easier to be killed by terrorists than to marry over 40.

762
01:17:39,850 --> 01:17:44,260
-胡说八道 -是，甜心
- That is not true! - Right, honey.

763
01:17:44,440 --> 01:17:49,900
我不要邮寄新娘 我只想找个人
I don't want a mail-order bride. Just someone who can converse...

764
01:17:50,070 --> 01:17:55,900
可以边吃饭边聊 不会因电影而大哭
...without falling into weepy tears over an old movie.

765
01:17:56,070 --> 01:18:02,110
看《The Dirty Dozen》结尾时我有哭 吉米·布朗丢手榴弹
I cried over The Dirty Dozen. Jim Brown throwing the grenades.

766
01:18:02,290 --> 01:18:07,910
理查德·杰柯和李·马文 乔扮纳粹
Richard Jaeckel and Lee Marvin on top of a tank dressed like Nazis.

767
01:18:09,630 --> 01:18:16,630
他们等着特里尼·洛佩兹 在跳伞时折断颈子
Trini Lopez... breaks his neck when they're parachuting.

768
01:18:16,800 --> 01:18:21,640
理查德·杰柯是宪兵 戴了钢盔
Richard Jaeckel had on a shiny helmet, because he was an MP.

769
01:18:21,810 --> 01:18:26,550
别再说了 我爱死那部电影
Please, no more. God, I love that movie.

770
01:18:34,950 --> 01:18:39,660
-这是我看过最棒的电影 -好在哪里？
- This is the best movie I ever saw. - What's so great about it?

771
01:18:39,830 --> 01:18:44,490
-你一定得找到她，乔纳 -你知道去纽约要多少钱吗？
- You have to find her. - How much would it cost to go?

772
01:18:44,670 --> 01:18:49,330
谁晓得，票价天天变
Nobody knows. It changes practically every day.

773
01:18:49,500 --> 01:18:52,790
-你有多少钱？ -80元
- How much money do you have? - 80 dollars.

774
01:18:52,970 --> 01:18:58,960
-我有42，计程车费可能够了 -可是我怎么去呢？
- I have 42. That'll cover cabs. - How would I get there?

775
01:18:59,140 --> 01:19:04,880
-我得去送票，你看一下家好吗？ -好，妈
I have to drop these tickets off. Can you keep an eye on things?

776
01:19:10,730 --> 01:19:12,440
(1993年2月14日 联合航空，航班号597)

777
01:19:12,610 --> 01:19:13,850
（纽约机场）

778
01:19:14,030 --> 01:19:15,060
（乔纳·鱼包德温）

779
01:19:15,240 --> 01:19:18,530
-靠窗还是走道？ -靠窗
- Window seat or aisle? - Window.

780
01:19:18,700 --> 01:19:23,490
要水果盘吗？ 我从不吃机上的食物
You want a fruit plate? I'd rather die than eat airplane food.

781
01:19:23,660 --> 01:19:27,950
我说你十二岁 才可单独飞行
I'll write you're 12. That way you can fly unaccompanied.

782
01:19:28,130 --> 01:19:34,710
-神经病！谁会相信？ -进了电脑，他们就会信
- Who'd believe I'm 12? - They'll believe the computer.

783
01:19:34,880 --> 01:19:40,350
我说你太矮 这样说你不会生气吧？
I'll say you're short for your age, but that they shouldn't mention it.

784
01:19:40,520 --> 01:19:42,760
好主意
Great idea!

785
01:19:43,150 --> 01:19:44,310
?Tammy Wynette: "Stand by Your Man"?

786
01:19:44,480 --> 01:19:49,690
?Sometimes it's hard to be a woman ?

787
01:19:52,660 --> 01:19:59,120
?Giving all your love to just one man ?

788
01:20:03,040 --> 01:20:06,910
-火车快开了 -不会赶不上
- You'll miss the train.  - No I won't.

789
01:20:07,080 --> 01:20:12,580
我好快乐，我终于快乐了 这才是正确真实
I'm so happy, Becky. This is right. It's real.

790
01:20:12,760 --> 01:20:17,920
其余只是看太多电影
The other things happen in movies.

791
01:20:18,100 --> 01:20:22,140
别跟别人说 我迷恋想像中的人
Don't tell anyone what I did. I'd die...

792
01:20:22,310 --> 01:20:28,730
那影响我的专业形象，保证？
...if anyone knew I did anything like that. You promise?

793
01:20:28,900 --> 01:20:32,510
西雅图夜未眠已成历史
Sleepless in Seattle is history.

794
01:20:32,510 --> 01:20:35,520
?... hard to understand ?

795
01:20:38,290 --> 01:20:41,330
?And if you love him ?

796
01:20:43,000 --> 01:20:46,500
?Oh, be proud of him ?

797
01:20:47,670 --> 01:20:53,090
?'Cause after all he's just a man ?

798
01:20:56,800 --> 01:20:59,470
?Stand by your man ?

799
01:21:05,560 --> 01:21:08,770
-说吧 -你先说
- Go ahead. - No, you go.

800
01:21:08,940 --> 01:21:13,180
我要说，自从圣诞节后
I was going to say that since Christmas...

801
01:21:13,360 --> 01:21:17,320
你变得有点分心
...you've been kind of distracted.

802
01:21:17,490 --> 01:21:23,780
但现在 你好像又回头了
But now it feels as if you're coming back from wherever you were.

803
01:21:23,960 --> 01:21:27,200
是的
